The paper deals with geometric algorithms, specifically for computing convex hulls and other standard problems in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses decision tree models and adversary arguments, which are common in the study of data structures (cs.DS) and complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also mentions distribution-sensitive data structures (cs.DM) and numerical algorithms (cs.NA), which are relevant to the analysis of geometric algorithms.
